Ahead of the 11th Triennial Conference of the African Potato Association happening in Kigali this season, CNBC Africa spoke to JanLow, World Food Prize Co-Laureate & Principal Scientist for the International Potato Centre on how sweet potatoes and other varieties of the root vegetable could be the solution to Africa's food security and agricultural woes. 

